HTML.

    HTML Stands fro Hyper Text Mark up language.

    HTML Used to Develop the Web Pages.


HTML Structure.

    - Declaration

    - Root Element

    - Head Section

    - Body Section


    - HTML Pages we will develop by using Element

        Ex.

            <html></html>

            <head></head>

                --
                --
                --

index.html
-
<!DOCTYPE html>

<html>
    <head>
        <title>My First Web Page</title>
    </head>

    <body>
        Welcome to First HTML Page
    </body>
</html>



1.<b> </b>  -- (bold)  used to make the text as bold

2.<i> </i>  --- (italic)  used to make the text as italic.

3.<font> </font>

4.<h1>......</h1>   to  <h6>.....</h6>    Headings

5.&nbsp;   -- single line space

6.&emsp;   -- tab space

7.<br></br>  -- single line break

8. <input>   -- Create the Input Elements like User Names , passwords , Numbers , ...

9.<label> </label>  -- used to create the labels in web application

10.<button> </button>  -- to create the buttons in web application.

11.<form></form>   -- used to create the form in web application.

    Ex.

        //Login Form.

        <form action="http://localhost:8080/myserver" method="post">

            <label>Email.</label>&emsp&emsp&emsp&emsp
            <input type="email" name="my_email">

            <br><br>
            <label>Password.</label>
            <input type="password" name="upwd">

            <br><br>
            <input type="submit"></input>

        </form>

12.<a> </a>

13.style

    - used to apply the css style to the HTML Elements

    - we can apply the styles in 2 ways.

        - inline css style

        - external css style



JavaScript.

      - javascript used to make the HTML As Dynamic.

      - it is a scripting language.